[{"id":"VH951399","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a sphere of a Van de Graaff generator that has a charge of uppercase Q. A small sphere, with a charge of lowercase q, is shown to the right of the Van de Graaff generator. The force experienced by the small sphere is represented by a rightward pointing arrow labeled F.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH951399.g07.png\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A small sphere with charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive lowercase q\"><math alttext=\"positive lowercase q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is used to test the electric field produced by the relatively large charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive uppercase Q\"><math alttext=\"positive uppercase Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> found on the surface of the sphere of a Van de Graaff generator. The small sphere experiences an electrostatic repulsion force <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F\"><math alttext=\"F\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> due to its interaction with the large sphere. In different trials, the charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive lowercase q\"><math alttext=\"positive lowercase q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is increased, the small sphere is placed the same distance from the large surface, and the resulting force <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F\"><math alttext=\"F\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is measured. Which of the following graphs best represents <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F\"><math alttext=\"F\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> as a function of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase q\"><math alttext=\"lowercase q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> ?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH951399_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a graph in the first quadrant of the coordinate plane with origin labeled O. The horizontal axis is labeled lowercase q and the vertical axis is labeled F. The line begins near the top of the vertical axis above the origin and moves downwards and to the right at a constant rate, ending at the rightmost point on the horizontal axis and approximately one quarter of the way up the vertical axis.\" height=\"147\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH951399.g02.png\" width=\"200\"></span></p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a graph in the first quadrant of the coordinate plane with origin labeled O. The horizontal axis is labeled lowercase q and vertical axis is labeled F. The line begins at the origin and moves diagonally upwards and to the right.\" height=\"147\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH951399.g03.png\" width=\"200\"></span></p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a graph in the first quadrant of the coordinate plane with origin labeled O. The horizontal axis is labeled lowercase q and the vertical axis is labeled F. The line begins at the origin and curves gradually upward and to the right at an increasing rate, ending at the rightmost point on the horizontal axis and at the top of the vertical axis.\" height=\"147\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH951399.g04.png\" width=\"200\"></span></p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a graph in the first quadrant of the coordinate plane with origin labeled O. The horizontal axis is labeled lowercase q and the vertical axis is labeled F. The line begins at the origin and curves steeply upward and to the right at a decreasing rate, ending at the rightmost point on the horizontal axis and at the top of the vertical axis.\" height=\"147\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH951399.g05.png\" width=\"200\"></span></p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a graph in the first quadrant of the coordinate plane with origin labeled O. The horizontal axis is labeled lowercase q and the vertical axis is labeled F. The line begins at the top of the vertical axis above the origin and curves steeply downward and to the right at a decreasing rate, ending at the rightmost point on the horizontal axis and just above the bottom of the vertical axis.\" height=\"147\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH951399.g06.png\" width=\"200\" /></span></p>\n"],"answer":1}]